<br>
The island is not KOS upon first entry, on the raid that got mine, everyone else was on the prior island so I just keyed over and did my thing, and looked at all the pretty horses before we brought everyone else over to kill some of them for other epic item drops.<br>
<br>
I have been told by a person in my guild that has a *lot* of experience leading Air raids that it can be done with one group.  However in the two Air raids I've been on we had our share of wipeouts with a lot more people than that.  <br>
<br>
I will say though that with Air, more people is not always better.  It's often less expensive and faster to do it with less if you can.  One of the biggest challenges in Air is not screwing anything up like pulling a boss mob early or something else that can end the raid.  Less people = less opportunity for things to go wrong.<br>
<br>
Recently we went to Air with a lot of people, ended up aggroing the boss mob on Island 2 early, getting wiped out, and he despawned (and GM wouldn't help us).  The next day we pulled a marathon 18 hour raid (starting with a smaller group and bringing more later for the tougher fights) and cleared up to and including the Drake Island (most people call that Island 7) for the mage epic.<br>
<br>
If you don't have people with a lot of Air raiding experience, particularly whoever is leading the raid, then you probably need 3-4 groups to get there.<br>
